                <td bgcolor="#5A71AD" valign="top"><font color="white" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/04/2003&nbsp;: 08:14:47 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> My experience:<br /><br />Take the Battlemaster and the Prophet camp.  Both are near Akheva Ruins zone line.  Directly out from the "dome" is a rock with 2 gorangas, that is the Battlemaster camp.  Bring a beastlord twink or something, some sweet shoulders drop here.  Once you kill those 2 go east over the hill.  At the bottom you'll see a 3 spawn of gorangas, this is the Prophet camp.  Slay these 3, run to the south side of the zone, med up and go read a book.  20-30 minutes later the first 2 will respawn.  Wash, rinse, repeat.<br /><br />Bottom line is this camp SUCKS.  Named are rare and highly contested, and the shard can only drop from the named ones AFAIK.  I got this one after about a 4-5 hour stretch of holding both camps I described.</span></font></td>
